# Optional: pre-configure a Groq API key server-side so the app works
# out of the box without users entering their own key.
#
# Set these two variables in your Vercel (or other host) dashboard:
#
#   GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_...
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_HAS_SERVER_KEY=true
#
# How it works:
#   - GROQ_API_KEY is a server-only variable. It is NEVER exposed to the
#     browser or bundled into client-side JavaScript.
#   - NEXT_PUBLIC_HAS_SERVER_KEY signals to the UI that a key is available
#     server-side, so the "Add API key" prompt is hidden and the mic button
#     is enabled on first load.
#   - If a user pastes their own key in Settings, it takes priority over the
#     server key for all requests from that browser.
#
# Both variables are optional. If neither is set, users must supply their
# own Groq key via the Settings modal. No .env file is required to run
# the app locally.
